{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"sage-rant-hinge","description":"# BUG: config-file mcp.readonly not honored by the LLM runner's comment tool\n\n## What\n`runner.py:566-571` `_readonly_gate` reads only env `REBAR_MCP_READONLY`; `mcp_server.py:208-223` is config-aware. A server made read-only via `[mcp] readonly=true` (env unset) hides MCP write tools but a `source=local` gate run still grants the review agent `comment_ticket` (`runner.py:219`, `pai_tools.py`).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Both surfaces resolve read-only through one config-aware helper (env wins over file, fail-closed).\n- [ ] Regression test: file-only readonly => the review agent's comment tool is withheld.\n- [ ] Commit carries a `rebar-ticket:` trailer.","id":"9d7a-d09d-835f-484c","parent_id":"9322-f84a-e047-4471","priority":1,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"BUG: config-file mcp.readonly not honored by the LLM runner's comment tool"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783056798195481001,"uuid":"584fc065-ddd6-4f07-9bff-fdebe30068a7"}